  "body": "/kind bug\r\n/sig api-machinery\r\n/cc @jennybuckley @apelisse \r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\npatching (SMP) any object's annotation using invalid patch content will result in an (500) internal-server error. expecting a (400) bad-request error in this case.\r\n\r\npatch body:\r\n```json\r\n{\"metadata\":{\"annotations\":{\"foo\":[\"bar\"]}}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nreceived error:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\"kind\":\"Status\",\"apiVersion\":\"v1\",\"metadata\":{},\"status\":\"Failure\",\"message\":\"unrecognized type: string\",\"code\":500}\r\n```\r\n\r\nthe error is thrown from converter instead of the patcher, so it seems that patcher considers the body as valid then the converter complained.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nwhen my grandpa was 65 years old he started running one mile a day to keep fit. he's 70 now and we have no idea where he is.",
